title: For Trade:  Walther  CCP 9mm
postcontent: Brand new Walther CCP  never fired? The CCP operates as a semi-auto because of its blowback system. Walther calls their design a delayed or “SoftCoil” (not re-coil) technology. This means of course that the pistol directs a portion of the gas pressure from an ignited cartridge through a tiny port in the barrel in front of the chamber to slow down and delay the rearward motion of the slide. A piston inside a cylinder under the barrel opposes the rearward motion of the slide until the gas pressure has subsided—after the bullet has left the barrel. At this point, the slide slams to its rear-most point, opens the breech, and ejects the empty cartridge case.

title: For Sale:  COLT Model 1911 45ACP BLACK ARMY Pistol
postcontent: This is an excellent condition all original Colt Model 1911 45ACP semi-automatic military pistol that was manufactured in 1918 with the 'Black Army' finish adopted by Colt to expedite production. Colt eliminated the final polishing steps on the M1911 pistols and the term Black Army is used to refer to the rough appearance to the blue finish. The black army pistols shipped between May 1918 and March 1919. The left side of the frame is marked 'UNITED STATES PROPERTY' and the eagle head over 'S8' above the magazine release. The left side of the slide is marked 'PATENTED APR.20,1897. SEPT.9,1902 over DEC.19,1905. FEB.14.1911. AUG.19.1913. on the left side of the ‘rampant colt’ and on the right side of that logo COLT'S PT.F.A.MFG.CO.' over HARTFORD,CT.U.S.A.. The serial number ‘No339233’ is stamped on the right side of the frame. The right side of the slide is marked 'MODEL OF 1911.U.S.ARMY'. An ‘H’ inspection mark is stamped on the rear of the slide above the firing pin stop. The top of the barrel chamber is stamped with an ‘H’ and a ‘P’. It is complete with a WWI two tone blue magazine. The grips are checkered with the large diamond pattern around the grip screws. They are in overall excellent condition with only minor signs of use. The pistol retains approximately 99% of the original 'Black Army' finish with only minor loss on the sharp edges and below the slide stop. This pistol would be an excellent addition to your Colt and/or U.S. military arms collection. Shipping will cost $30 REDACTED
